# Goose Hints — Eric's Engineering Constitution

This repository follows [Eric's Engineering Constitution](constitution/CONSTITUTION.md). Apply it on every task, including when goose runs under a multi-agent orchestrator such as goosetown.

## Installing goose and goosetown

Neither ships with this repository — both are separate CLI tools you run
this repo's work through, not something Claude Code (or any single-file
hint like this one) can install on their own. If `goose --version` fails,
the one-shot fix is `bash constitution/scripts/setup-machine.sh
--skip-gstack` (run once per machine, idempotent). Or by hand:

```bash
# goose CLI (org is aaif-goose, formerly published under block/)
curl -fsSL https://github.com/aaif-goose/goose/releases/download/stable/download_cli.sh | bash
```

For multi-agent orchestration (a flock of goose delegates working in
parallel — researchers, workers, writers, reviewers):

```bash
git clone https://github.com/aaif-goose/goosetown.git
cd goosetown && ./goose
```

goosetown requires goose v1.25.0+ already installed. See
[aaif-goose/goose](https://github.com/aaif-goose/goose) and
[aaif-goose/goosetown](https://github.com/aaif-goose/goosetown) for full
docs — their own READMEs still say `block/...` in places (pre-rename;
GitHub redirects it, but clone the `aaif-goose/...` URL directly).

## Required Reading

Before making changes, read:

1. `constitution/CONSTITUTION.md` — Universal Principles.
2. `constitution/AI_WORKFLOW.md` — Required step-by-step workflow.
3. `AGENTS.md` — Project-specific rules and overrides.
4. `README.md`, `TODO.md`, `CHANGELOG.md` — Project context.
5. `docs/MEMORY.md` — Project memory (learnings, preferences, decisions).

## Standards

- Follow the workflow in `constitution/AI_WORKFLOW.md` for every task.
- Check `docs/SESSION_PLAN.md` for a previous interrupted session, then write your own plan before implementing.
- Read `docs/MEMORY.md` to load project context, codebase learnings, and user preferences.
- Add or update tests for behavioral changes; evaluate coverage and record gaps.
- Update `TODO.md` and `CHANGELOG.md` as part of every change.
- Record major design decisions in `docs/adr/`.
- Review security impact before completing work.
- Propose new codebase learnings, user preferences, or major decisions to the user and (upon approval) record them in `docs/MEMORY.md` before completing work.

## Multi-Agent Orchestration (goosetown)

When goose agents run in parallel, every researcher, worker, writer, and reviewer is bound by this constitution. Reviewers must check changes against `constitution/TESTING.md`, `constitution/SECURITY.md`, and `constitution/DOCUMENTATION.md` before approving, and the project-specific rules in `AGENTS.md` win over universal defaults.

## MCP Extension

The constitution ships an MCP server at `constitution/mcp-server/`. Register it as a goose stdio extension to load the constitution documents as resources and to validate project structure. See the "Goose and Goosetown" section of `constitution/INTEGRATION.md` for setup.
